title: Omicron vs Delta: The Entry Mechanism

scenes.voiceover: Why is Omicron so contagious but less severe than Delta? The answer lies in how it breaks in.
scenes.visual_description: Cinematic wide shot in a dark void. Two distinct viral particles float in suspension. On the left, the Delta variant glows with an aggressive fiery red aura and sharp, jagged spike proteins. On the right, the Omicron variant glows with a sleek, ice-blue light. Volumetric lighting highlights the texture of their lipid envelopes. Slow camera push-in.

scenes.voiceover: Delta was a brute. It used a surface enzyme called TMPRSS2 to fuse directly with your lung cells.
scenes.visual_description: Extreme close-up on a cell surface, rendered with hyper-realistic wet biological texture. The Red Delta virus approaches. Its spike protein locks mechanically onto a metallic-looking surface receptor labeled TMPRSS2. The connection sparks like a welding torch, causing the viral membrane to violently merge and fuse with the cell membrane. High contrast lighting.

scenes.voiceover: But Omicron? It lost the key to that door. Instead, it gets swallowed whole, sneaking in through a bubble called the endosome.
scenes.visual_description: The Blue Omicron virus approaches the same cell surface. It bounces off the TMPRSS2 receptor, unable to latch on. Instead, the cell membrane gently indents and wraps around the virus, encapsulating it in a translucent, glossy bubble (an endosome) which drifts silently into the cell's interior. Soft, mysterious backlighting.

scenes.voiceover: Because it can't fuse membranes, Omicron fails to melt cells together into destructive zombie blobs.
scenes.visual_description: Split screen comparison. Left side (Delta): Dozens of cells are melting together into one terrifying, giant, pulsating blob with multiple glowing nuclei (Syncytia). Right side (Omicron): Cells remain distinct, round, and separate, arranged in a neat healthy lattice. Dramatic color grading.

scenes.voiceover: It evolved to spread fast and dodge immunity, but lost the weapon that destroys lungs. A deadly trade-off.
scenes.visual_description: Sweeping dolly shot zooming out from the healthy cells. Thousands of blue Omicron particles swarm rapidly across the screen, filling the frame like a blizzard. The background tissue remains intact but is covered in the blue viral swarm. Fade to black.
